{"success": true, "message": "Fetched question.", "data": {"hasAccess": false, "showTimer": true, "showAttemptInsight": true, "playSounds": true, "dontShowCorrectAnswerImmediately": false, "_id": "648b5a6d417cc3fb48d67ac0", "classes": [], "exams": ["615d76b2c52ffa3c944600df"], "subjects": ["615d708dbd4a37c4058ee5a8"], "chapters": ["615d6fed2b295b085ab6eb9a"], "topics": [], "concepts": [], "previousYearPapers": [{"_id": "63134c746e7bc9b332483705", "title": "JEE Main 2022 (27 Jul Shift 1)", "isVisible": true}], "type": "singleCorrect", "level": 2, "approximateTimeRequired": 180, "question": {"text": "Two identical positive charges <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>Q</mi></math> each are fixed at a distance of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mi>a</mi></math>&nbsp;apart from each other. Another point charge <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>q</mi><mn>0</mn></msub></math> with mass <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>m</mi></math>&nbsp;is placed at midpoint between two fixed charges. For a small displacement along the line joining the fixed charges, the charge <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>q</mi><mn>0</mn></msub></math> executes SHM. The time period of oscillation of charge <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>q</mi><mn>0</mn></msub></math> will be", "image": null}, "options": [{"id": "kojR7", "text": "<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msqrt><mfrac><mrow><mn>4</mn><msup><mi>&#960;</mi><mn>3</mn></msup><msub><mi>&#949;</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mi>m</mi><msup><mi>a</mi><mn>3</mn></msup></mrow><mrow><msub><mi>q</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mi>Q</mi></mrow></mfrac></msqrt></math>", "isCorrect": true, "image": null}, {"id": "qRVYl", "text": "<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msqrt><mfrac><mrow><msub><mi>q</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mi>Q</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>4</mn><msup><mi>&#960;</mi><mn>3</mn></msup><msub><mi>&#949;</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mi>m</mi><msup><mi>a</mi><mn>3</mn></msup></mrow></mfrac></msqrt></math>", "isCorrect": false, "image": null}, {"id": "egHbR", "text": "<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msqrt><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><msup><mi>&#960;</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><msub><mi>&#949;</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mi>m</mi><msup><mi>a</mi><mn>3</mn></msup></mrow><mrow><msub><mi>q</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mi>Q</mi></mrow></mfrac></msqrt></math>", "isCorrect": false, "image": null}, {"id": "gvgKx", "text": "<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msqrt><mfrac><mrow><mn>8</mn><msup><mi>&#960;</mi><mn>3</mn></msup><msub><mi>&#949;</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mi>m</mi><msup><mi>a</mi><mn>3</mn></msup></mrow><mrow><msub><mi>q</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mi>Q</mi></mrow></mfrac></msqrt></math>", "isCorrect": false, "image": null}], "correctValue": null, "solution": {"text": "<blockquote><p><img src=\"https://cdn-question-pool.getmarks.app/pyq/jee_main/c4cc5ffd-4e6c-4bd7-967f-6091be0cf637-1b833bce-44a7-4fda-bf61-d9df17d1fa51-image.png\" style=\"width: 250px; height: 125px;\" /></p><p>Let the charged particle be displaced slightly towards right by distance <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>&#8810;</mo><mi>d</mi></mrow></mfenced></math>.</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mi>Q</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>a</mi><mi>t</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>A</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>q</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>:</mo><msub><mi>F</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mrow><mn>4</mn><mi>&#960;</mi><msub><mi>&#949;</mi><mn>0</mn></msub></mrow></mfrac><mfrac><mrow><mi>Q</mi><mi>q</mi></mrow><msup><mfenced><mrow><mi>d</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup></mfrac></math>, towards right</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mi>Q</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><mtext>at</mtext><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>B</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>q</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>:</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><msub><mi>F</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mrow><mn>4</mn><mi>&#960;</mi><msub><mi>&#949;</mi><mn>0</mn></msub></mrow></mfrac><mfrac><mrow><mi>Q</mi><mi>q</mi></mrow><msup><mfenced><mrow><mi>d</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup></mfrac></math>, towards left</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#160;</mo><msub><mover><mi>F</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo></mover><mrow><mi>n</mi><mi>e</mi><mi>t</mi></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><msub><mover><mi>F</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo></mover><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>+</mo><msub><mover><mi>F</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo></mover><mn>2</mn></msub></math>, will bring it towards <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>O</mi></math>.<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mover><mi>F</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo></mover><mrow><mi>n</mi><mi>e</mi><mi>t</mi></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mrow><mn>4</mn><mi>&#960;</mi><msub><mi>&#1013;</mi><mn>0</mn></msub></mrow></mfrac><mfenced close=\"]\" open=\"[\"><mrow><mfrac><mn>1</mn><msup><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mfenced><mrow><mi>d</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfenced></mstyle><mn>2</mn></msup></mfrac><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><msup><mfenced><mrow><mi>d</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup></mfrac></mrow></mfenced><mover><mi>i</mi><mo>^</mo></mover></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mo>-</mo><mi>Q</mi><mi>q</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>4</mn><mi>&#960;</mi><msub><mi>&#1013;</mi><mn>0</mn></msub></mrow></mfrac><mfenced close=\"]\" open=\"[\"><mfrac><mrow><mn>4</mn><mi>x</mi><mi>d</mi></mrow><msup><mfenced><mrow><msup><mi>d</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup></mfrac></mfenced><mover><mi>i</mi><mo>^</mo></mover></math></p><p>Since <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>&#8810;</mo><mi>d</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></math> is negligible.</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mover><mi>F</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo></mover><mrow><mi>n</mi><mi>e</mi><mi>t</mi></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mfenced><mfrac><mrow><mi>Q</mi><mi>q</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>&#960;</mi><msub><mi>&#1013;</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><msup><mi>d</mi><mn>3</mn></msup></mrow></mfrac></mfenced><mo>&#215;</mo><mi>x</mi><mover><mi>i</mi><mo>^</mo></mover></math></p><p>Clearly, the direction of the force is opposite to the displacement &amp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>F</mi><mo>&#8733;</mo><mi>x</mi></math>, hence it is an SHM.</p><p>Acceleration of charged particle is given as,</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>a</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>F</mi><mi>m</mi></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>Q</mi><mi>q</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>&#960;</mi><msub><mi>&#1013;</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mi>m</mi><msup><mi>d</mi><mn>3</mn></msup></mrow></mfrac><mi>x</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mfenced><mn>1</mn></mfenced></math></p><p>And we know that for SHM,</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>a</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><msup><mi>&#969;</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mi>x</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#8230;</mo><mo>.</mo><mfenced><mn>2</mn></mfenced></math></p><p>Comparing <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mn>1</mn></mfenced></math>&nbsp;and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mn>2</mn></mfenced></math>, we get</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>&#969;</mi><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mfrac><mrow><mi>Q</mi><mi>q</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>&#960;</mi><msub><mi>&#1013;</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mi>m</mi><msup><mi>d</mi><mn>3</mn></msup></mrow></mfrac></msqrt></math></p><p>Hence, the&nbsp;time period,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>T</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>&#960;</mi></mrow><mi>&#969;</mi></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>&#960;</mi><msqrt><mfrac><mrow><mi>&#960;</mi><msub><mi>&#1013;</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mi>m</mi><msup><mi>d</mi><mn>3</mn></msup></mrow><mrow><mi>Q</mi><mi>q</mi></mrow></mfrac></msqrt></math></p><p>Therefore,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>T</mi><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mfrac><mrow><mn>4</mn><msup><mi>&#960;</mi><mn>3</mn></msup><msub><mi>&#949;</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mi>m</mi><msup><mi>a</mi><mn>3</mn></msup></mrow><mrow><msub><mi>q</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mi>Q</mi></mrow></mfrac></msqrt></math></p></blockquote>", "image": null}, "videoSolution": {"videoId": "22b11243437a4ad6ae2cb1c3a6271a0d", "provider": "vdocipher", "thumbnailLight": "https://d1z78r8i505acl.cloudfront.net/poster/TnstwPIq4NAzU.480.jpeg", "thumbnailDark": "https://d1z78r8i505acl.cloudfront.net/poster/TnstwPIq4NAzU.480.jpeg", "premiumModules": [{"premiumModuleId": "6628114842d540dfcb148ecb", "isFree": false}, {"premiumModuleId": "64c7e8e829737784b294e469", "isFree": false}, {"premiumModuleId": "6788cc0b2dbc1ecacabb7026", "isFree": false}], "description": "JEE Main"}, "questionLabels": [], "masterId": "MOGJMPYQ87995956", "source": "EM", "bucket": "Must Do Ques (JEE Main) - Any Difficulty", "numericalLowerLimit": null, "numericalUpperLimit": null, "category": null, "microConcepts": [], "imageBaseUrl": null, "helperText": null, "isRemoved": false, "cpyqbSubjects": ["61bb58181213731910ea0b70", "61c055eae8ce0dc8a5c62d33", "616057750283de43c87e3e1b", "61964fe0a5a5260118868021", "61964f81a5a526011886801d", "629f39e4ac11b26562e0625b", "616057920283de43c87e3e1e", "615f0c729476412f48314dab", "61a8a2c2e8ce0dc8a5c62d2d", "629105adee9e3ae00d63352b", "629f385f263330a77be9fa7d", "616056cd0283de43c87e3e15", "616057190283de43c87e3e18", "62962075e7f8e9ac4daeafd7", "64d50bd73df7f4a7f3017f6f", "66b79b34d4b564dfab4f94cc", "678ea9a09cc79e5f592bdc11", "67fa5fef4468eb1307ceb0ad", "6807d2ad647479b8e8696479"], "